author: THE NEWS HERALD sports@pcnh.com
title: Arnold sweeps NBH 3-0
text: Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 9:46 PM Updated at 9:48 PM PANAMA CITY BEACH â€” Arnold earned its second win of the week Wednesday night by knocking off North Bay Haven 25-19, 25-14, 25-15 to improve to 12-6 on the season. Casey Justice and Eden Hawes led the way for the Marlins with 11 kills each, with Justice adding seven digs, three aces, and a block, and Hawes 30 digs and an ace. Gabby Crowley had a big night with 30 assists, eight digs, three aces, two blocks, and three kills, with Gabby Fisher contributing seven kills, three blocks, five digs, and two aces. McKinley Hart had five kills and a block. Sydney Painter recorded a kill and four blocks. The Marlins will next play at Mosley on Thursday at 6 p.m. The Buccaneers fell to 8-9 on the season and next play host to West Florida on Friday. By THE NEWS HERALD
